Speaker 1: it off file, actually.

Speaker 2: You said that you canceled.

Speaker 1: Yeah. I told them I didn't want them no more, and then a couple, three months later, they

Speaker 2: took that on my credit card, so I just wanted everything...

Speaker 1: Yeah. It looks like here, I do see the recorded call that you did when you called in, and

Speaker 2: it looks like you, because it all is transcribed, it looks like you spoke to the guy and you

Speaker 2: I told them I'd send it back, and they would credit my... Yeah, I told them I'd send it

Speaker 2: Okay. But I do see a note that you spoke to someone, and you guys decided to pause it

Speaker 2: Yeah. I don't want it no more. I'm done with it.

Speaker 1: No, I understand. So that's not what I'm describing. I'm describing that you was told that this

Speaker 2: was going to be paused for five months, and I see here that you did agree with that.

Speaker 1: Oh. Well, I guess I misunderstood, because I wanted to pause until I was ready for some

Speaker 2: more if I want.

Speaker 1: Correct. That's what was done for you, but...

Speaker 2: But I never called them and told them I wanted more.

Speaker 1: Well, it doesn't last forever, so it does usually do that in six-month periods, so we

Speaker 2: can keep your prescription open for you.

Speaker 1: Oh, yeah. I want to cancel. I don't want them no more.

Speaker 2: All right. Well, you are already canceled, sir. Anything else that you need?

Speaker 1: No. So you've canceled me, and they won't be sending me no more, or trying to...

Speaker 2: You've actually been canceled since the 5th of this month. I believe you called already.

Speaker 1: Did you call again?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I called, but I didn't know if they got me canceled or what they got done. I just

Speaker 1: want to make sure it's done.

Speaker 2: Yeah, they canceled.

Speaker 1: Okay. So I won't be getting no more pills, and they won't be sending me no more, right?

Speaker 2: No, sir. You will never receive this again. You are canceled, and your prescription is

Speaker 1: You're welcome.
